In the waiting room of every health centre, you see immigrants.
How much easier would a Brit get medical appointments if they weren't there?
Every school has children of immigrants.
How much easier would the children of a real Brit get a school place if they got rid of them?
Every town has foreigners.
How much more space would the natives have if they bailed?
I think these are economic issues.
They concern jobs, housing and public services.
But economists failed to respond to them and, if they did, their responses received no visibility.
